  "prompt": "What are the names of the specific executives at Marvel and Fox that are preventing X-Men & Fantastic Four characters from appearing in the Marvel Cinematic Universe?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, specific names of executives at Marvel and Fox who were directly involved in preventing X-Men and Fantastic Four characters from appearing in the Marvel Cinematic Universe (MCU) aren't publicly detailed. \n\nHowever, prior to Disney's acquisition of 21st Century Fox in 2019, the rights to the X-Men and Fantastic Four characters were held by Fox. During that time, decisions regarding the use of these characters were made by Fox executives. Key figures at Fox included people like **Simon Kinberg**, who was a producer and writer for the X-Men films, and **Alan Horn**, who previously held significant roles at Disney and was involved with the larger franchise direction.\n\nPost-acquisition, with Marvel Studios under the leadership of **Kevin Feige**, the company has been strategically integrating these characters into the MCU. Nevertheless, the specifics around negotiations and timelines can often involve multiple layers of executive decision-making and legalities that aren't always publicly disclosed.\n\nIf you're interested in updates beyond October 2023, I would recommend checking recent news sources for any new developments regarding the integration of X-Men and Fantastic Four characters into the MCU.",
